    <p>Sus­tain­abil­ity has been nudged up on the na­tional agenda this year, with Sin­ga­pore an­nounc­ing plans to tackle cli­mate change and cre­ate jobs in the sus­tain­abil­ity sec­tor. In this episode of Green Pulse, en­vi­ron­ment cor­re­spon­dent Au­drey Tan speaks with Na­tional Devel­op­ment Min­is­ter Des­mond Lee on how Covid-19 has high­lighted the im­por­tance of sus­tain­abil­ity, and what his min­istry plans to do to make Sin­ga­pore's built en­vi­ron­ment cooler and greener.</p>
    <p>Find out more by scan­ning this episode us­ing our QR code. str.sg/JWaf</p>

